Welcome to octapps, the unofficial LSC octave-script repository.

This is currently available via git with the following command:

git-clone gitanon@n0.aei.uni-hannover.de:~repr/git-public/octapps.git

To use these routines, add the following to your .bashrc

export OCTAPPS_TOP=<path-to-your-octapps-git-dir>
OCTAPPSRC=${OCTAPPS_TOP}/SDE/octapps.sh
if [ -f "${OCTAPPSRC}" ]; then
    source ${OCTAPPSRC} ${OCTAPPS_TOP}
fi

or the following to your .cshrc:

setenv OCTAPPS_TOP ${HOME}/lscsoft/octapps
setenv OCTAPPSRC ${OCTAPPS_TOP}/SDE/octapps.csh
if ( -f ${OCTAPPSRC} ) then
    source ${OCTAPPSRC} ${OCTAPPS_TOP}
endif

If you also use matapps, it's probably important to add the octapps
activation above AFTER any matapps activation in your .bashrc or
.cshrc
